@@eThornwood@@N

Thornwood is a @@rnecrotic estate-forest@@N south of the Great Northern
Forest's canopy edge: part abandoned noble domain, part predatory
woodland intelligence, part ossuary production system. Its defining
trait is @@rassimilation@@N -- the manor did not disappear into wilderness,
nor did the wilderness merely overgrow architecture. Both were
metabolized into one procedural ecology that treats death as input.

Four inseparable logics govern the estate. @@yManorial logic@@N persists
in gates, titles, hereditary symbols, and protocols of entry and
exclusion. @@dFunerary logic@@N drives barrows, charnel verges, and
exhumation-reinterment cycles that process bone as material resource.
@@gForest logic@@N expresses itself through root pressure, adaptive
pathing, canopy suppression, and biological territorial response. And
beneath it all, @@lsubstrate logic@@N -- a crystalline geological
formation predating human settlement -- mediates the necrotic ecology
that makes Thornwood dangerous.

The Harren Charter established a fortified manor here during
Midgaard's Founding Generation, displacing ridge-clan burial customs
of face-down oathbreaker graves and thorn-ring containment growth.
As Midgaard's burial infrastructure overflowed, the estate became a
death-processing facility. Ritual specialists became production
foremen. The dead were routed, not received.

Among the estate's lowest laborers, the @@rRoot Covenant@@N crystallized:
a substrate theology that rejected chapel bells in favor of confession
spoken into the earth at root-contact points. Blood opens listening
channels. Roots carry memory farther than paper. Bone remembers debt
when ledgers fail.

When Lord Harren invited the cult into his administrative structure
and commissioned exploration of the crystal caves below, the
@@rReversal Event@@N crossed a threshold. Roots grew toward ritual sites
from hundreds of meters away. The dead rose with bark-textured skin
and thorn-growth through joints. The forest read the manor's
blueprints and replicated them in biological material.

Lord Harren did not flee. He was @@rretained@@N -- an estate revenant
with complete awareness, trapped inside a system he helped create.
The @@dThornwood Lich@@N emerged from the substrate itself, a geological
intelligence maintaining a biological binding now @@rfailing@@N. The
@@rWild Hunt@@N -- the estate's mobile enforcement arm -- has extended
its patrol range farther toward the Lantern Road than in any prior
generation.
